properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 7 at 9:57PM CST until January 8 at 8:00AM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...A PERIOD OF LAKE EFFECT SNOW WILL DEVELOP THIS EVENING AND
CONTINUE INTO WEDNESDAY MORNING...

.Colder air will continue to filter into the region in the wake
of a cold front tonight. This cold air will help support some
lake effect snow showers over the higher terrain of Iron County in
northwest Wisconsin, beginning this evening and persisting into
Wednesday morning. This snow could impact the Wednesday morning
commute for the Kimball, Montreal, Gile, and Hurley areas. This
cold air and breezy winds will also lead to very cold wind chills
tonight across most of northeastern Minnesota with readings of -25
to -35 degrees expected.

More snow will develop Wednesday night into Thursday. The highest
accumulation is expected along portions of the North Shore which
may see 6 inches or more.

* WHAT...Lake effect snow with additional snow accumulation of 1
to 3 inches.

* WHERE...Iron County.

* WHEN...Until 8 AM CST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
Road conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or
511wi.gov for Wisconsin.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 AM CST WEDNESDAY
